Stain and fix gel overnight in 10% Acetic acid, 24%
Isopropanol, 0.1% Coomassie Blue.
Destain gel at least 2 hrs. the next day in 10%
Acetic acid, 24% Isopropanol. When bands are
visible soak gel for 1/2 hr. in AMPLIFY. Remove gel
and dry on gel dryer for about 1 hr. Place gel over
X-Ray film in -70 deg. freezer (AMPLIFY will not
work at room temperature).
By the end of the day the RNA gel should be
sufficiently exposed for developing; The film can
be developed by hand or with an automatic X-ray
processor. Densitometry can then be done on the
film if a densitometer is available.
If all goes well the translation product gel will be
ready for developing in about 2 days.
GOOD
